University Research System

A comprehensive Java console application for managing academic and research activities at a university. The system handles course registration, student grading, research paper management, journal subscriptions, and technical support ticketing.

Overview

The University Research System is designed to support multiple user roles with different responsibilities and permissions. Students register for courses with credit limits, teachers manage courses and input grades, managers approve registrations and oversee the system, researchers publish papers and calculate impact metrics, and administrators manage users and system logs.

The system implements professional object-oriented design patterns including Singleton for centralized data storage, Decorator for flexible researcher roles, Observer for journal notifications, and Strategy for flexible sorting algorithms.

