Design Patterns

The system implements four major design patterns as required by project specifications:

1. Singleton Pattern - DataStorage
Ensures exactly one data storage instance exists throughout program execution. All system components access the same DataStorage.getInstance() to maintain data consistency. Alternative approaches like passing storage as parameters everywhere would create tight coupling.

2. Decorator Pattern - Researcher Role
Allows adding researcher capability to any user (Teacher or Student) without modifying their class hierarchy. ResearcherDecorator wraps User objects and adds research methods. TeacherResearcher and StudentResearcher are concrete decorators. This solves the problem that Java lacks multiple inheritance but users can be both teachers and researchers.

3. Observer Pattern - Journal Notifications
Implements automatic notification when papers are published to journals. Journal is Observable, Users are Observers. When a paper is published, journal calls notifyObservers which sends notifications to all subscribers. This decouples publishers from subscribers and scales well.

4. Strategy Pattern - Paper Sorting
Allows flexible sorting of research papers using interchangeable comparators. CitationComparator, DateComparator, and LengthComparator each implement the Strategy. The printPapers method takes a Comparator as parameter and sorts accordingly. Adding new sort strategies requires only new Comparator class without modifying existing code.

Key Constraints

Student Registration Constraints
- Maximum 21 total credits per semester (throws CourseOverloadException)
- Cannot fail same course more than 3 times (throws CourseFailLimitException)
- Cannot have scheduling conflicts between lessons

Research Constraints
- Only Researchers can join ResearchProject (throws NotResearcherException)
- GraduateStudent supervisors must have h-index at least 3 (throws LowHIndexException)

Academic Constraints
- Teachers with position PROFESSOR are always researchers
- Professors can publish papers and calculate h-index
- Master and PhD students (GraduateStudents) are always researchers
- Regular students and other teachers can optionally become researchers

