Custom Exceptions

The system uses custom exceptions to signal specific error conditions:

CourseOverloadException
Thrown when student tries to register for courses exceeding 21 credit limit. Signals that operation violates academic policy.

CourseFailLimitException
Thrown when student has failed course three times and attempts to register again. Signals that student has exhausted retake attempts.

LowHIndexException
Thrown when trying to assign supervisor to graduate student if supervisor's h-index is below 3. Signals that supervisor does not meet qualification requirements.

NotResearcherException
Thrown when non-researcher tries to join research project. Signals that participant does not have required researcher status.

All custom exceptions extend RuntimeException (unchecked) to signal logic errors that should fail fast and require code fixes.

