Data is saved to text files in the data/ directory:
- users.txt: All user accounts
- courses.txt: Course catalog
- enrollments.txt: Student registrations
- marks.txt: Student grades
- papers.txt: Research papers
- projects.txt: Research projects
- journals.txt: Academic journals
- news.txt: News items
- messages.txt: User communications
- logs.txt: System activity log

Files are automatically created on first save. Format uses semicolon delimiter with special character escaping for newlines and semicolons in content.

Technical Architecture

Object Oriented Principles
- **Low Coupling**: User classes do not directly depend on DataStorage. Interfaces define contracts.
- **High Cohesion**: Each class has single responsibility. User classes handle user behavior, storage classes handle persistence.
- **DRY**: Common functionality is in base classes. Specific behavior in subclasses.
- **Liskov Substitution**: Employee subclasses can be used anywhere Employee is expected.

Design Patterns Applied
- Singleton: DataStorage
- Decorator: ResearcherDecorator
- Observer: Journal notifications
- Strategy: Comparators

Exception Handling
- Custom exceptions for constraint violations
- Try-catch blocks for file I/O
- Fail-fast approach for invalid operations

